RELEASE_NOTE:
*Issue Description:*
Following the upgrade to the Jackson JARs from version 2.15.2 to 2.19.2, an error is being thrown when making REST API calls for file downloads that contain binary data (Blob objects).
*User Interface Impact:* No
*Steps to Reproduce:*
# Upload a blob file (like an image) via a File Upload API e.g. {{/v1/dbs/files}}
# Attempt to get File Contents via API e.g. {{/v1/dbs/files/:fileId}} without specifying an Accept header
# Issue: An InvalidDefinitionException is thrown: {{InvalidDefinitionException: No serializer found for class curam.util.type.Blob}}

*Resolution:*
Ensure the correct {{Accept}} header is provided for API calls when downloading binary files:
{noformat}GET /v1/dbs/files/:fileId
Accept: application/octet-stream{noformat}

*JavaScript/Fetch API:*
{noformat}fetch('/v1/dbs/files/123', {  
  headers: {
    'Accept': 'application/octet-stream'
  }
}){noformat}

*cURL:*
{noformat}curl -H ""Accept: application/octet-stream"" /v1/dbs/files/123{noformat}

*Java HTTP Client:*
{noformat}HttpRequest request = HttpRequest.newBuilder()
    .uri(URI.create(""/v1/dbs/files/123""))
    .header(""Accept"", ""application/octet-stream"")
    .build();{noformat}
